label.value: Patient Navigator

value.value: Persons who are trained to guide and support those requiring assistance obtaining medical care. Such persons are sensitive to socio-economic factors within the community and provide a variety of services. Their primary responsibilities are to assist patients that have an abnormal examination or a positive finding to navigate through the health care system.

label.value: Fellowship for the Interpretation of Genomes

value.value: A non-profit organization specializing in bioinformatics tool development and comparative genomics research.

label.value: Correlation

value.value: The degree to which two or more quantities or events are linearly associated, a statistical relation between two or more variables such that systematic changes in the value of one variable are accompanied by systematic changes in the others.

label.value: Role

value.value: The usual or expected function of something; the part something plays in an action or event.

label.value: 78 kDa Glucose-Regulated Protein

value.value: 78 kDa glucose-regulated protein (654 aa, ~72kDa) is encoded by the human HSPA5 gene. The protein is intracellularly localized in the endoplasmic reticulum lumen, and plays a role in the assembly of multimeric protein complexes inside the organelle. In addition, the protein is thought to function as a pro-survival protein, or an inhibitor of apoptosis.

label.value: HSPA5 Gene

value.value: This gene is involved in cellular signal transduction.

label.value: Cutaneous Melanoma Pathologic TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of cutaneous melanoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system. TNM pathologic findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

label.value: Cutaneous Melanoma pTX TNM Finding v6

value.value: Cutaneous melanoma in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Benign Neck Neoplasm

value.value: A neoplasm that arises from the neck region and is characterized by the absence of atypical or malignant cytological and architectural features, and absence of invasive features or metastatic potential.

label.value: Cutaneous Melanoma pT0 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Cutaneous melanoma with no evidence of primary tumor. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Cutaneous Melanoma pTis TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Cutaneous melanoma in situ. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Cutaneous Melanoma pT1 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Cutaneous melanoma 1.0mm or less in thickness, with or without ulceration. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Cutaneous Melanoma pT1a TNM Finding v6

value.value: Cutaneous melanoma 1.0mm or less in thickness and Clark level II or III, with no ulceration. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Cutaneous Melanoma pT1b TNM Finding v6

value.value: Cutaneous melanoma 1.0mm or less in thickness, with ulceration and/or Clark level IV or V. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Cutaneous Melanoma pT2 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Cutaneous melanoma 1.01 to 2 mm in thickness, with or without ulceration. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Cutaneous Melanoma pT2a TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Cutaneous melanoma 1.01 to 2 mm in thickness, with no ulceration. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Cutaneous Melanoma pT2b TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Cutaneous melanoma 1.01 to 2 mm thick, with ulceration. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Cutaneous Melanoma pT3 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Cutaneous melanoma 2.01 to 4 mm thick, with or without ulceration. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Cutaneous Melanoma pT3a TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Cutaneous melanoma 2.01 to 4 mm in thickness, with no ulceration. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Cutaneous Melanoma pT3b TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Cutaneous melanoma 2.01 to 4 mm thick, with ulceration. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Cutaneous Melanoma pT4 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Cutaneous melanoma greater than 4.0 mm in thickness, with or without ulceration. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Cutaneous Melanoma pT4a TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Cutaneous melanoma greater than 4.0 mm in thickness, without ulceration. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Cutaneous Melanoma pT4b TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Cutaneous melanoma greater than 4.0 mm in thickness, with ulceration. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Cutaneous Melanoma pNX TNM Finding v6

value.value: Cutaneous melanoma in which the regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Cutaneous Melanoma pN0 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Cutaneous melanoma without involvement of regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Cutaneous Melanoma pN1 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Cutaneous melanoma with involvement of one lymph node. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Cutaneous Melanoma pN1a TNM Finding v6

value.value: Cutaneous melanoma with microscopic, clinically occult metastasis to a single lymph node. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Cutaneous Melanoma pN1b TNM Finding v6

value.value: Cutaneous melanoma with macroscopic, clinically apparent metastasis to a single lymph node. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Cutaneous Melanoma pN2 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Cutaneous melanoma involving two to three regional lymph nodes, or involving the regional intra-lymphatic system without nodal involvement. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Benign Pyriform Fossa Neoplasm

value.value: A neoplasm that arises from the pyriform sinus and is characterized by the absence of atypical or malignant cytological and architectural features, and absence of invasive features or metastatic potential.

label.value: Cutaneous Melanoma pN2a TNM Finding v6

value.value: Cutaneous melanoma with microscopic, clinically occult metastasis to two or three regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Cutaneous Melanoma pN2b TNM Finding v6

value.value: Cutaneous melanoma with macroscopic, clinically apparent metastasis to two or three regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Cutaneous Melanoma pN2c TNM Finding v6

value.value: Cutaneous melanoma without involvement of regional lymph nodes, with satellite or in-transit metastasis. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Cutaneous Melanoma pN3 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Cutaneous melanoma involving four or more regional lymph nodes, or with a finding of matted metastatic nodes, or with in-transit metastasis or satellite(s) with metastasis in regional lymph node(s). (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Cutaneous Melanoma pM0 TNM Finding

value.value: Cutaneous melanoma with no evidence of distant metastasis. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Cutaneous Melanoma pMX TNM Finding

value.value: Cutaneous melanoma in which the status of distant metastasis cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Cutaneous Melanoma pM1 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Cutaneous melanoma with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Cutaneous Melanoma pM1a TNM Finding v6

value.value: Cutaneous melanoma with metastasis to skin, subcutaneous tissues or distant lymph nodes. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Cutaneous Melanoma pM1b TNM Finding v6

value.value: Cutaneous melanoma with metastasis to lung. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Cutaneous Melanoma pM1c TNM Finding

value.value: Cutaneous melanoma with metastases to all other visceral sites associated with normal serum lactate dehydrogenase (LDH) or distant metastases to any site associated with an elevated serum LDH. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Metastatic Malignant Neoplasm in the Trachea

value.value: A malignant neoplasm that has spread to the trachea from another anatomic site.

label.value: Double

value.value: A 64-bit floating point primitive. When wrapped in an immutable Object, it is called a Double.

label.value: Date Data Type

value.value: A string unique to a time duration of 24 hours between 2 successive midnights defined by the local time zone. The specific representation of a date will depend on which calendar convention is in force as well as local ordering conventions.

label.value: Kinesin-Like Protein KIF11

value.value: Kinesin-like protein KIF11 (1056 aa, ~119 kDa) is encoded by the human KIF11 gene. This protein plays a role in the formation of a bipolar spindle during mitosis.

label.value: Splenic Lymphoma

value.value: A non-Hodgkin lymphoma or rarely Hodgkin lymphoma that arises from the spleen.

label.value: Swallow Evaluation

value.value: The administration of liquids in assorted thicknesses to determine the ability of a patient to swallow without aspiration.  Swallow evaluation involves a variety of approaches, but may be divided into endoscopic and non-endoscopic techniques.

label.value: Cartilage-Like Elements Present
Dedifferentiated Chordoma

value.value: A high-grade malignant bone tumor arising from the remnants of the notochord. It is characterized by a lobulated growth pattern, myxoid stroma formation, the presence of physaliphorous cells, and a sarcomatous component.

Neoplastic Lipoblast
